<h2 id="scope">Scope</h2>
<p>This guidance is tool-agnostic and applies regardless of platform. It covers common charts and graphs used to communicate structured data in digital products, including bar charts, line charts, scatter plots and similar formats. It applies to both public-facing services and internal dashboards.</p>

<h3>Out of scope</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Expressive infographics designed for campaigns or marketing</li>
  <li>Advanced analytical visualisations such as network graphs or complex relationship mapping</li>
  <li>Interactive GIS mapping</li>
  <li>Highly specialised investigative tools built for internal compliance work</li>
</ul>
<p>Where technical limitations exist, teams must document the limitation and provide an accessible alternative where possible.</p>


<h2 id="principles">Principles</h2>
<p>Use these principles as your pre-flight checklist before publishing any graph.</p>
