<h2 id="match-the-chart-to-the-task">Match the chart to the task</h2>
<p>Every chart must answer a clear question. Choose the chart type based on the relationship you need to show: comparison, trend, distribution or correlation. If users need precise values, provide a table.</p>

<div class="nsw-grid nsw-m-top-sm">
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--do"><span class="material-icons nsw-material-icons" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">check_circle</span><span>Do use when</span></div>
    <ul>
      <li>Comparing categories</li>
      <li>Showing change over time</li>
      <li>Showing distribution</li>
      <li>Showing correlation between variables</li>
      <li>Helping users quickly see patterns or trends</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--dont"><span class="material-icons nsw-material-icons" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">cancel</span><span>Don't use when</span></div>
    <ul>
      <li>A single number communicates the message</li>
      <li>A table is clearer</li>
      <li>The dataset is too small</li>
      <li>The chart requires heavy explanation</li>
      <li>It is used for decoration</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>


<h2 id="choosing-the-right-chart">Choosing the right chart</h2>
<p>Choose the simplest chart that matches the data relationship.</p>

