<p><strong>Excluded:</strong> Yellow 02 (<code>#FAAF05</code>) is <code>1.88:1</code> on white and is not compliant for chart marks.</p>
<p class="nsw-docs__pattern-swatch-note">In a few 02 rows, the line colour uses White or 01 to keep pattern contrast at or above <code>3:1</code>.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Start with 01 and 02 from your main colour theme.</li>
  <li>If more colours are needed, add additional colour columns using 01 first, then 02.</li>
  <li>For a series of charts, keep category colours consistent across all charts so users can follow the story.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Aboriginal palette chart-mark options (3:1+ on white)</h4>
<div class="nsw-section nsw-section--white nsw-block nsw-p-x-sm nsw-p-top-sm">
  <div class="nsw-table nsw-table--valign-middle">
    <table class="nsw-docs__chart-colour-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="width: 9%">Swatch (plain)</th>
          <th style="width: 29%">Colour value</th>
          <th style="width: 12%">Contrast ratio on white</th>
          <th style="width: 9%">Swatch (pattern)</th>
          <th style="width: 29%">Line value</th>
          <th style="width: 12%">Pattern contrast</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
